CHESTS
------

Each chest contains objects of a given level; this level is set at
the time of the chest's generation.  This object generation level is set
to a random integer between 1 and the level of the chest.  Chests may also
be trapped, with the danger posed by the traps generally increasing with
the chest's object generation level.

Small chests contain one item, and large chests contain two items.  (Ruined
or already opened chests contain no items.)  Items found in small chests
may be either objects or treasure, while large chests always have objects,
never treasure.  Chests may not contain other chests.

All chests have a rarity of 1, and can be thrown for the indicated damage.

